    "source_commit": "8fec14c",
    "notes": [
      "JS lifecycle oracle proof for source Game.onStop() continuing instead of ending when multiple present avatars are tied at max score.",
      "The harness starts a real all-present 3P source round with max_score 1, waits for delayed PrintManager.start timers, forces avatar 3 to die first, then forces avatars 2 and 1 to die together in the next source update.",
      "Because Game.update() captures deaths.count() at frame start, avatars 2 and 1 both resolve to score 1; source isWon() sees tied leaders at max score and starts the next round instead of emitting end.",
      "This is only the focused tie-at-max-score continuation proof; it does not claim broad multi-round match, broader present/non-present, broader 4P, vector lifecycle, or trainer/replay/final-observation behavior."
    ]
  },
